Daily Crypto Decode | Apr 8
US-Iran two-week ceasefire → BTC sees its largest price surge since March 18
Heading into last weekend, sentiment was overwhelmingly bearish — traders had been piling into short positions, expecting no breakthrough between the US and Iran.
Then on Tuesday afternoon, Trump announced a two-week ceasefire agreement. With short positions carrying unlimited downside risk, traders were forced to buy immediately once prices started moving up — purely to cut their losses.
That wave of forced buying is what drove the short-term BTC price surge.
